        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13594#pullrequestreview-4453981726\">PR review</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Mind updating <code>docs/stability-tiers.md</code> too?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 601266708,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1780959352
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13594#discussion_r3376809838\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For this, can this be added to <code>WasmFeatures</code> unconditionally? That way rec-groups and such will all works as expected and it's just GC-bearing things that fail at runtime when gc is disabled at compile-time.</p>\n<p>In theory <code>GC_TYPES</code> should be the only cnoditional-based-on-compile-time feature we need</p>\n</blockquote>",
